{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I've been working on issues of poverty for more than 20 years,"},{"time":4000,"text":"and so it's ironic that the problem that and question that I most grapple with"},{"time":9000,"text":"is how you actually define poverty. What does it mean?"},{"time":12000,"text":"So often, we look at dollar terms --"},{"time":14000,"text":"people making less than a dollar or two or three a day."},{"time":16000,"text":"And yet the complexity of poverty really has to look at"},{"time":21000,"text":"income as only one variable."},{"time":23000,"text":"Because really, it's a condition about choice,"},{"time":25000,"text":"and the lack of freedom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"And I had an experience that really deepened and elucidated for me"},{"time":30000,"text":"the understanding that I have."},{"time":32000,"text":"It was in Kenya, and I want to share it with you."},{"time":34000,"text":"I was with my friend Susan Meiselas, the photographer,"},{"time":36000,"text":"in the Mathare Valley slums."},{"time":38000,"text":"Now, Mathare Valley is one of the oldest slums in Africa."},{"time":41000,"text":"It's about three miles out of Nairobi,"},{"time":43000,"text":"and it's a mile long and about two-tenths of a mile wide,"},{"time":46000,"text":"where over half a million people"},{"time":48000,"text":"live crammed in these little tin shacks,"},{"time":50000,"text":"generation after generation, renting them,"},{"time":53000,"text":"often eight or 10 people to a room."},{"time":55000,"text":"And it's known for prostitution, violence, drugs:"},{"time":61000,"text":"a hard place to grow up."},{"time":63000,"text":"And when we were walking through the narrow alleys,"},{"time":65000,"text":"it was literally impossible not to step in the"},{"time":68000,"text":"raw sewage and the garbage alongside the little homes."},{"time":72000,"text":"But at the same time it was also"},{"time":74000,"text":"impossible not to see the human vitality,"},{"time":77000,"text":"the aspiration and the ambition of the people who live there:"},{"time":80000,"text":"women washing their babies, washing their clothes, hanging them out to dry."},{"time":83000,"text":"I met this woman, Mama Rose,"},{"time":85000,"text":"who has rented that little tin shack for 32 years,"},{"time":88000,"text":"where she lives with her seven children."},{"time":90000,"text":"Four sleep in one twin bed,"},{"time":92000,"text":"and three sleep on the mud and linoleum floor."},{"time":95000,"text":"And she keeps them all in school by selling water from that kiosk,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and from selling soap and bread from the little store inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103000,"text":"It was also the day after the inauguration,"},{"time":105000,"text":"and I was reminded how Mathare is still connected to the globe."},{"time":109000,"text":"And I would see kids on the street corners,"},{"time":111000,"text":"and they'd say \"Obama, he's our brother!\""},{"time":113000,"text":"And I'd say \"Well, Obama's my brother, so that makes you my brother too.\""},{"time":116000,"text":"And they would look quizzically, and then be like, \"High five!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"And it was here that I met Jane."},{"time":123000,"text":"I was struck immediately by the kindness and the gentleness in her face,"},{"time":126000,"text":"and I asked her to tell me her story."},{"time":129000,"text":"She started off by telling me her dream. She said, \"I had two."},{"time":132000,"text":"My first dream was to be a doctor,"},{"time":134000,"text":"and the second was to marry a good man"},{"time":136000,"text":"who would stay with me and my family,"},{"time":138000,"text":"because my mother was a single mom,"},{"time":140000,"text":"and couldn't afford to pay for school fees."},{"time":142000,"text":"So I had to give up the first dream, and I focused on the second.\""},{"time":146000,"text":"She got married when she was 18, had a baby right away."},{"time":149000,"text":"And when she turned 20, found herself pregnant with a second child,"},{"time":153000,"text":"her mom died and her husband left her -- married another woman."},{"time":157000,"text":"So she was again in Mathare, with no income, no skill set, no money."},{"time":161000,"text":"And so she ultimately turned to prostitution."},{"time":164000,"text":"It wasn't organized in the way we often think of it."},{"time":166000,"text":"She would go into the city at night with about 20 girls,"},{"time":169000,"text":"look for work, and sometimes come back with a few shillings,"},{"time":172000,"text":"or sometimes with nothing."},{"time":174000,"text":"And she said, \"You know, the poverty wasn't so bad. It was the humiliation"},{"time":177000,"text":"and the embarrassment of it all.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"In 2001, her life changed."},{"time":183000,"text":"She had a girlfriend who had heard about this organization, Jamii Bora,"},{"time":187000,"text":"that would lend money to people no matter how poor you were,"},{"time":190000,"text":"as long as you provided a commensurate amount in savings."},{"time":194000,"text":"And so she spent a year to save 50 dollars,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and started borrowing, and over time she was able to buy a sewing machine."},{"time":202000,"text":"She started tailoring."},{"time":203000,"text":"And that turned into what she does now,"},{"time":206000,"text":"which is to go into the secondhand clothing markets,"},{"time":208000,"text":"and for about three dollars and 25 cents she buys an old ball gown."},{"time":212000,"text":"Some of them might be ones you gave."},{"time":214000,"text":"And she repurposes them with frills and ribbons,"},{"time":218000,"text":"and makes these frothy confections that she sells to women"},{"time":222000,"text":"for their daughter's Sweet 16 or first Holy Communion --"},{"time":226000,"text":"those milestones in a life that people want to celebrate"},{"time":229000,"text":"all along the economic spectrum."},{"time":231000,"text":"And she does really good business. In fact, I watched her"},{"time":234000,"text":"walk through the streets hawking. And before you knew it,"},{"time":236000,"text":"there was a crowd of women around her, buying these dresses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240000,"text":"And I reflected, as I was watching her sell the dresses,"},{"time":243000,"text":"and also the jewelry that she makes,"},{"time":245000,"text":"that now Jane makes more than four dollars a day."},{"time":248000,"text":"And by many definitions she is no longer poor."},{"time":251000,"text":"But she still lives in Mathare Valley."},{"time":253000,"text":"And so she can't move out."},{"time":256000,"text":"She lives with all of that insecurity,"},{"time":258000,"text":"and in fact, in January, during the ethnic riots,"},{"time":261000,"text":"she was chased from her home and had to find a new shack"},{"time":263000,"text":"in which she would live."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265000,"text":"Jamii Bora understands that and understands"},{"time":267000,"text":"that when we're talking about poverty,"},{"time":269000,"text":"we've got to look at people all along the economic spectrum."},{"time":272000,"text":"And so with patient capital from Acumen and other organizations,"},{"time":275000,"text":"loans and investments that will go the long term with them,"},{"time":278000,"text":"they built a low-cost housing development,"},{"time":282000,"text":"about an hour outside Nairobi central."},{"time":286000,"text":"And they designed it from the perspective of"},{"time":288000,"text":"customers like Jane herself,"},{"time":290000,"text":"insisting on responsibility and accountability."},{"time":292000,"text":"So she has to give 10 percent of the mortgage --"},{"time":296000,"text":"of the total value, or about 400 dollars in savings."},{"time":300000,"text":"And then they match her mortgage to what she paid in rent for her little shanty."},{"time":305000,"text":"And in the next couple of weeks, she's going to be"},{"time":307000,"text":"among the first 200 families to move into this development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"When I asked her if she feared anything,"},{"time":314000,"text":"or whether she would miss anything from Mathare,"},{"time":316000,"text":"she said, \"What would I fear"},{"time":318000,"text":"that I haven't confronted already?"},{"time":320000,"text":"I'm HIV positive. I've dealt with it all.\""},{"time":324000,"text":"And she said, \"What would I miss?"},{"time":327000,"text":"You think I will miss the violence or the drugs? The lack of privacy?"},{"time":330000,"text":"Do you think I'll miss not knowing if my children are going to come home"},{"time":332000,"text":"at the end of the day?\" She said \"If you gave me 10 minutes"},{"time":334000,"text":"my bags would be packed.\""},{"time":336000,"text":"I said, \"Well what about your dreams?\""},{"time":339000,"text":"And she said, \"Well, you know,"},{"time":341000,"text":"my dreams don't look exactly like I thought they would when I was a little girl."},{"time":345000,"text":"But if I think about it, I thought I wanted a husband,"},{"time":349000,"text":"but what I really wanted was a family"},{"time":352000,"text":"that was loving. And I fiercely love my children, and they love me back.\""},{"time":356000,"text":"She said, \"I thought that I wanted to be a doctor,"},{"time":359000,"text":"but what I really wanted to be was somebody"},{"time":361000,"text":"who served and healed and cured."},{"time":364000,"text":"And so I feel so blessed with everything that I have,"},{"time":367000,"text":"that two days a week I go and I counsel HIV patients."},{"time":371000,"text":"And I say, 'Look at me. You are not dead."},{"time":374000,"text":"You are still alive. And if you are still alive you have to serve.'\""},{"time":377000,"text":"And she said, \"I'm not a doctor who gives out pills."},{"time":381000,"text":"But maybe me, I give out something better"},{"time":383000,"text":"because I give them hope.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"And in the middle of this economic crisis,"},{"time":389000,"text":"where so many of us are inclined to pull in"},{"time":392000,"text":"with fear, I think we're well suited to"},{"time":396000,"text":"take a cue from Jane and reach out,"},{"time":399000,"text":"recognizing that being poor doesn't mean being ordinary."},{"time":403000,"text":"Because when systems are broken,"},{"time":405000,"text":"like the ones that we're seeing around the world,"},{"time":407000,"text":"it's an opportunity for invention and for innovation."},{"time":410000,"text":"It's an opportunity to truly build a world"},{"time":413000,"text":"where we can extend services and products"},{"time":416000,"text":"to all human beings, so that they can"},{"time":419000,"text":"make decisions and choices for themselves."},{"time":421000,"text":"I truly believe it's where dignity starts."},{"time":423000,"text":"We owe it to the Janes of the world."},{"time":426000,"text":"And just as important, we owe it to ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":431000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}